- and seethe like the River Styx. But there's something missing, isn't there?
Cut the shit, Mizora. How dare you force me to make such an impossible choice?
Ready and waiting.

EditorData.logicalname: Had final discussion after Wyll chose

Text.Value: You dug your own hole, pup. I merely supplied the claws.
It's a win-win.
You've been my private hellhound and hunter, Wyll - ever so eager. But I've seen something new:
So what's our first order of business, sir duke?
You are such a piece of shit, Mizora.
For now, you've tipped the scales in your favour. But all it takes is a whisper for me to tip them back.
It was good for me. Was it good for you?
You're as cunning as a fox. It's a delight to see you in action.
The fire of Avernus courses through you. And you know only I can bear it.
Far from it. I'm positively wrecked to see my poor Wyll orphaned like this.
Ah, the thrill of the unknown. I can't wait to see how this epic plays out.
Oh dear - the pangs of remorse. Is it our night you regret, or the fact we were caught?
The Nine Hells of Baator. Each its own domain, each with its own archdevil to rule it.
You have the best ideas.
I certainly did. Wyll's father is safe, and Wyll's free of you at last.
The Blade of Avernus. How marvellous - it rolls right off the tongue.

EditorData.logicalname: AVATAR: Wyll is Blade of Avernus

Synopsis: Mizora goes to players camp whether or not Wyll keeps the pact.
